    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nWhen there is an ext mark with virtual lines outside of the current displayed area, and you scroll to it with for example `<C-f>`, this assertion is false https://github.com/neovim/neovim/blob/8cca7871555e15f53de3dc4325c8d0203a78622a/src/nvim/decoration.c#L891\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n`nvim --clean`\r\n\r\n```\r\n100o\r\n<ESC>\r\ngg\r\n\r\n:lua vim.api.nvim_buf_set_extmark(1, vim.api.nvim_create_namespace \"foo\", 100, 0, { virt_lines = { { { \"hello world\", \"Normal\" } } } })\r\n\r\n<C-f>\r\n```\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nThis shouldn't fail.\n\n### Neovim version (nvim -v)\n\nNVIM v0.10.0-dev-2873+g8cca78715\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nNo\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nArch Linux\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nkitty 0.33.0\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nxterm-kitty\n\n### Installation\n\nbuild from repo",
    "closed_at": "2024-04-12T22:18:47Z",
